
1
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:35,700
BISM ALLAH ARRAHMAN ARRAHIM
My dear lucky viewers, Al-Salaamu ‘Alaykum

2
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:42,239
This tape will present to you how to observe
the Contact Prayer, the Salat.

3
00:02:42,239 --> 00:02:49,379
And you are very lucky because you are trying
to learn how to make contact with your creator,

4
00:02:49,379 --> 00:02:51,680
which is the greatest of all worships.

5
00:02:52,403 --> 00:02:56,980
In this tape, I will explain to you the meaning
of the word Salat.

6
00:02:56,980 --> 00:02:59,711
You already heard me call it contact.

7
00:02:59,711 --> 00:03:05,060
The word Salat (&rlm;صلاة) is an Arabic
word derived from the root Silah (صلة),

8
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:11,499
which means connection or contact. So, when
you observe the Salat prayers, you make contact

9
00:03:11,499 --> 00:03:12,680
with your creator.

10
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:16,620
It is wrong to translate it as pray.

11
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:23,018
As a Muslim, when you tell somebody “I pray
five times a day”, that is the wrong expression,

12
00:03:23,018 --> 00:03:26,730
because other people can tell you “I pray
all day.”

13
00:03:26,730 --> 00:03:34,269
The correct expression for the Muslim is “I
make contact with my creator five times a

14
00:03:34,269 --> 00:03:35,269
day.”

15
00:03:35,269 --> 00:03:37,870
This is the meaning of Salat.

16
00:03:37,870 --> 00:03:44,450
In this program, I will present to you where
the Salat commandment comes from.

17
00:03:44,450 --> 00:03:50,238
The Contact Prayer is mention in the Quran
more than seventy times.

18
00:03:50,238 --> 00:03:58,999
And I will show you the crucial verses, like
where the times of Contact Prayers are mentioned

19
00:03:58,999 --> 00:04:00,543
in the Quran.

20
00:04:00,543 --> 00:04:06,209
Then, I will go on to explain to you the source
of the Contact Prayers.

21
00:04:06,209 --> 00:04:12,660
When was the first time that the contact commandment
came to us from God? And how did it come to

22
00:04:12,660 --> 00:04:16,395
our generation? I will explain this to you.

23
00:04:16,395 --> 00:04:22,230
Then, I will move on to explain why does God
want us to establish contact with Him.

24
00:04:22,230 --> 00:04:27,620
Why did God command us to observe the Contact
Prayers five times a day?

25
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:29,392
What is the reason?

26
00:04:29,392 --> 00:04:34,630
Does God need the Contact Prayers, or do we
need the Contact Prayers?

27
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:42,950
After this, I will go on to explain every aspect
of the Contact Prayer.

28
00:04:42,950 --> 00:04:47,950
I’m gonna start with the call for the
Contact Prayer, the Azan (أَذَان).

29
00:04:47,950 --> 00:04:52,230
I will go through the details, even the historical
development of it.

30
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:57,684
I will show you how the words are written
in English, the English transliteration.

31
00:04:57,684 --> 00:05:03,410
Then, I will go on to the preparation for the
Contact Prayers, which is called Wuḍū (وضوء&lrm;)

32
00:05:03,410 --> 00:05:05,060
or ablution.

33
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:08,100
And of course, my sources are always the Quran.

34
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:14,270
There's only one source, and it is this book
right here, the Quran.

35
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:18,220
God’s message to you, to me and to the whole
world.

36
00:05:18,220 --> 00:05:21,119
This is God’s final message to the world.

37
00:05:21,119 --> 00:05:25,500
And this is our source, the only source.

38
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:41,829
I will show you where the Wuḍū is mentioned
in Quran and what the details are.

39
00:05:41,829 --> 00:05:46,274
Then, I will demonstrate for you how to do
the Wuḍū.

40
00:05:46,274 --> 00:05:52,359
And I will move on from there to demonstrate
for you and describe in detail how to do the

41
00:05:52,359 --> 00:05:55,872
five daily Contact Prayers.

42
00:05:55,872 --> 00:06:03,740
The Morning Contact, the Noon Contact
Prayer, the afternoon, the sunset, and the

43
00:06:03,740 --> 00:06:04,910
night Contact Prayer.

44
00:06:04,910 --> 00:06:13,650
I will explain also some of the fine details
of... for example, what happens when you miss

45
00:06:13,650 --> 00:06:16,540
part of the Contact Prayer in a group.

46
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:21,470
You're going to the mosque and you see a group of
people praying, you come in late, what to do?

47
00:06:21,470 --> 00:06:24,240
And some other fine detail.

48
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:30,320
So, I hope this will cover everything you need
to know about the Contact Prayer.

49
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:33,300
The most important worship in Islam.

50
00:07:06,340 --> 00:07:13,260
You heard me say that the Contact Prayers
must be observed five times every day.

51
00:07:13,260 --> 00:07:18,439
Okay, where in the Quran do you find these
five times?

52
00:07:18,439 --> 00:07:22,020
They are specifically defined in the Quran.

53
00:07:22,020 --> 00:07:29,020
For example, in Sura number 11, AYA
or verse number 114,

54
00:07:29,020 --> 00:07:32,990
we see three times of Contact Prayers.

55
00:07:32,990 --> 00:07:39,710
This is what the verse says “You shall
observe the Contact Prayers at both ends of

56
00:07:39,710 --> 00:07:42,670
the day, and at night.”

57
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:45,270
So, here you have three prayer.

58
00:07:45,270 --> 00:07:51,400
At both ends of the day, this is the Morning
Prayer and the Sunset Prayer.

59
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:59,050
The Morning Prayer is before sunrise and the
Sunset Prayer is immediately after sunset.

60
00:07:59,050 --> 00:08:03,560
And of course, the Night prayer is the last
prayer of the day.

61
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:09,164
So, here in this verse, we have three prayers.
We are commanded to do these three prayers.

62
00:08:09,164 --> 00:08:12,460
The Morning, the Sunset and the Night.

63
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:20,970
Now, the Noon Prayer is mentioned in Sura
number 17, verse number 78

64
00:08:20,970 --> 00:08:26,810
where it says “You shall observe
the Contact Prayer when the sun begins to

65
00:08:26,810 --> 00:08:31,310
decline from the highest point at noon.”

66
00:08:31,310 --> 00:08:38,139
So, this is a very specific description of
the time of the Contact Prayer at noon.

67
00:08:38,139 --> 00:08:44,183
As soon as the sun begins to decline from
its highest spot of the day at noon, you observe

68
00:08:44,183 --> 00:08:46,796
the Noon Contact Prayer.

69
00:08:46,796 --> 00:08:55,666
This is Sura 17, verse 78. It says exactly the time of the Contact Prayer at noon.

70
00:08:55,666 --> 00:09:00,379
So, now we see the Morning Prayer, the Noon Prayer,

71
00:09:00,379 --> 00:09:03,050
the Sunset Prayer, and the Night Prayer.

72
00:09:03,050 --> 00:09:07,660
Well, this accounts for 4 of the prayers.
Where is the fifth one?

73
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:13,009
We find the fifth prayer mentioned in
Sura number 2, AYA or verse number

74
00:09:13,009 --> 00:09:17,839
238), two three eight, where it says “You shall observe

75
00:09:17,839 --> 00:09:22,660
all the Contact Prayers, especially the middle
prayer.”

76
00:09:22,660 --> 00:09:27,119
The middle contact prayer has to be the Afternoon Prayer because we have the Morning

77
00:09:27,119 --> 00:09:31,074
Prayer, the Noon
Prayer, the Sunset Prayer, and the Night Prayer.

78
00:09:31,074 --> 00:09:34,639
These two prayers here and two prayers
here, so the middle prayer will be

79
00:09:34,639 --> 00:09:36,220
the Afternoon Prayer.

80
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:41,760
So, there you have it, all 5 Contact
Prayers mentioned in the Quran.

81
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:47,959
By the way, the Morning Prayer and the
Night Contact Prayer are mentioned by name

82
00:09:47,959 --> 00:09:52,525
in verse 58 of Sura 24.

83
00:09:52,525 --> 00:09:55,040
Sura 24, the verse is 58.

84
00:09:55,040 --> 00:10:01,149
It talks about Salat Al-fajr (صلاة الفجر&lrm;).
This is the Morning Contact Prayer, and Salat

85
00:10:01,149 --> 00:10:05,056
Al-isha (صلاة العشاء). This is the
Night Contact Prayer.

86
00:10:05,056 --> 00:10:12,000
So, all five times of the Contact Prayers are
decreed in the Quran.

87
00:12:10,327 --> 00:12:17,749
And now I would like to discuss with you the
source, the original source, of the Contact Prayers.

88
00:12:17,749 --> 00:12:25,636
When you look in the Quran, you will notice
that before Abraham, there was no mention of

89
00:12:25,636 --> 00:12:28,970
the Contact Prayers, the Salat.

90
00:12:28,970 --> 00:12:34,199
You notice that Noah was telling his people
to just believe in God and ask His forgiveness,

91
00:12:34,199 --> 00:12:38,640
but there is no mention of the Contact Prayers
before Abraham.

92
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:45,509
So, the original source of the Contact Prayers
is the prophet Abraham who is the father,

93
00:12:45,509 --> 00:12:47,629
the founder of Islam.

94
00:12:47,629 --> 00:12:53,800
And we see this very clearly in Sura number 22, verse number 78,

95
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:57,484
the last verse of Sura number 22.

96
00:12:57,484 --> 00:13:02,726
We also see it in Sura 21, verse 73

97
00:13:02,726 --> 00:13:11,610
where we learn that the Contact Prayers were
given to Abraham, as the original founder

98
00:13:11,610 --> 00:13:13,095
of Islam.

99
00:13:13,095 --> 00:13:18,529
And we see in Sura 16, verse number 123 that the prophet

100
00:13:18,529 --> 00:13:21,439
Muhammad followed the ways of Abraham.

101
00:13:21,439 --> 00:13:27,538
And then we see in Sura number 8
verses 33 to 35,

102
00:13:27,538 --> 00:13:33,279
and in Sura 9, verse 54,
we see that the Salat, the Contact Prayers,

103
00:13:33,279 --> 00:13:36,953
were practiced before the prophet Muhammad.

104
00:13:36,953 --> 00:13:42,588
So, all these... you know, a lot of people
are under the erroneous impression that the

105
00:13:42,588 --> 00:13:47,740
prophet Muhammad brought these practices,
but they came through prophet Abraham, and this

106
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:53,339
is why we do not see the details of how many
units per prayer and these kind of details,

107
00:13:53,339 --> 00:13:55,190
we do not find it in the Quran.

108
00:13:55,190 --> 00:14:00,000
Although the Quran is complete, perfect, and
fully detailed.

109
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:07,110
So, the reason the details of the Contact Prayers
are not in the Quran is because they were

110
00:14:07,110 --> 00:14:12,209
already in existence when the Quran was revealed.

111
00:14:12,209 --> 00:14:17,287
I can tell you to go and buy Crest toothpaste, and you will... I don’t

112
00:14:17,287 --> 00:14:22,689
have to explain to you what Crest toothpaste
is because Crest is already in existence,

113
00:14:22,689 --> 00:14:26,267
all you need to do is go out in the market
and buy it.

114
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:32,619
And when the Quran came down, the Contact
Prayers, the Salat, were already in existence.

115
00:14:32,619 --> 00:14:38,859
And this is exactly why in one of the very
early Suras, Sura number 73

116
00:14:38,859 --> 00:14:43,939
Al-Muzzammil,
we see the commandment to observe the Contact

117
00:14:43,939 --> 00:14:48,699
Prayers and the Zakat (the Obligatory Charity),
because they were already in existence.

118
00:14:48,699 --> 00:14:55,045
Abraham being the founder of Islam, what
did he contribute to the religion?

119
00:14:55,045 --> 00:14:59,294
He contributed all the practices of the religion.

120
00:14:59,294 --> 00:15:05,685
The Contact Prayer, The Zakat charity, The fasting of Ramadan. In fact, we see

121
00:15:05,685 --> 00:15:13,190
that the fasting of Ramadan was slightly modified
in the Quran in Sura number 2, verse 187.

122
00:15:13,190 --> 00:15:18,420
Also, Hajj. Hajj
in Sura number 22, we see that

123
00:15:18,420 --> 00:15:22,869
it is directly decreed through the prophet
Abraham.

124
00:15:22,869 --> 00:15:27,899
So, Abraham contributed all practices in Islam.
You must correct that impression.

125
00:15:27,899 --> 00:15:31,690
The prophet Muhammad contributed the Quran. That’s it.

126
00:15:31,690 --> 00:15:37,679
But all the practices existed before the prophet
Muhammad. They were in existence when the

127
00:15:37,679 --> 00:15:39,571
Quran came down.

128
00:15:51,884 --> 00:15:55,290
Now, we get to the question "why should we pray?"

129
00:15:55,290 --> 00:16:00,000
Why should we make contact with our creator
every day, five times?

130
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,759
Repeating the same thing, five times a day?

131
00:16:03,759 --> 00:16:08,579
Well, the answer... the obvious answer
first is that we do it because our creator

132
00:16:08,579 --> 00:16:12,759
commanded us to do so, in the Quran, as I
showed you.

133
00:16:12,759 --> 00:16:20,839
But what is the mechanism? Why does God ask
us to contact Him five times a day?

134
00:16:20,839 --> 00:16:22,629
Does God benefit from it?

135
00:16:22,629 --> 00:16:24,869
Do we benefit from it?

136
00:16:24,869 --> 00:16:31,306
And the answer immediately is "God does not need our Contact Prayer. We need the Contact Prayer."

137
00:16:31,306 --> 00:16:39,739
And we fully understand the reason for decreeing
the Contact Prayers if we know who we are.

138
00:16:39,739 --> 00:16:42,491
You see, most people do not even know who
they are.

139
00:16:42,491 --> 00:16:46,420
You ask a person “who are you?” and
they look in the mirror.

140
00:16:46,420 --> 00:16:49,639
They say “this is me.” And you know something? They are wrong.

141
00:16:49,639 --> 00:16:53,300
This is not me. This is my body.

142
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:57,716
And the body is like a garment that we are
wearing temporarily.

143
00:16:57,716 --> 00:17:04,225
The real person is invisible to us. The real
person, the soul, is in another dimension

144
00:17:04,225 --> 00:17:07,374
that is not visible to our eyes.

145
00:17:07,374 --> 00:17:10,334
So, what does the real person look like?

146
00:17:10,334 --> 00:17:15,959
This will lead us to understanding why should
we observe the Contact Prayer.

147
00:17:15,959 --> 00:17:23,852
You see, you can consider the Contact Prayers
the meals for the real person, the food, the nutrition.

148
00:17:23,852 --> 00:17:28,126
When we are born our mother feeds us milk
and we grow.

149
00:17:28,126 --> 00:17:34,250
Then, we eat all kinds of food, rice and meat
and potatoes and so on, and our body grows

150
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:38,134
until it becomes five feet, six feet, whatever.

151
00:17:38,134 --> 00:17:41,070
And that is the limit of the body’s growth.

152
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:45,800
Okay. Meanwhile, what is happening to the
real person, the soul?

153
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:53,874
The body or the garment grows to five or six feet, but what happens to the real person?

154
00:17:53,874 --> 00:17:58,014
Is the real person nourished just like the
body?

155
00:17:58,014 --> 00:18:06,116
And this is where most people do not realize
the importance of making contact with their creator.

156
00:18:06,116 --> 00:18:11,716
Making contact with our creator is the most
important nutrition for the soul.

157
00:18:11,716 --> 00:18:18,060
We need it to grow and develop. And I'm talking here
about the real person.

158
00:18:18,060 --> 00:18:24,994
The real person grows and develops by contacting
our creator daily.

159
00:18:24,994 --> 00:18:29,550
Five times every day constitutes five meals
for the soul.

160
00:18:29,550 --> 00:18:34,346
So, every time you do a Contact Prayer, your
soul grows and develops.

161
00:18:34,346 --> 00:18:38,509
And this is why we are commanded to do the
Contact Prayer.

162
00:18:38,509 --> 00:18:45,877
You can imagine the person who does not feed
his or her soul. At the end of living in this

163
00:18:45,877 --> 00:18:50,890
world, they are still babies because they
never feed their soul.

164
00:18:50,890 --> 00:18:56,690
But the Muslim, the person who observes
the duties and practices of worship,

165
00:18:56,690 --> 00:19:01,364
this person feeds the soul, and the soul grows
and develops immensely.

166
00:19:01,364 --> 00:19:08,916
And we end up our mission in this world, grown
and developed, and healthy, and fit for the

167
00:19:08,916 --> 00:19:12,869
real life, the eternal life that comes after
this life.

168
00:19:12,869 --> 00:19:22,150
The Contact Prayers therefore are very important.
Think of them as the meal for the soul, for the real person.

169
00:19:22,150 --> 00:19:28,770
The Morning Prayer is the breakfast for the soul,
for you, the real you. Just like how you give

170
00:19:28,770 --> 00:19:34,756
your body breakfast, lunch and dinner, you
need, for yourself, the real person, you

171
00:19:34,756 --> 00:19:37,050
need meals also.

172
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:40,164
The Noon Prayer is lunch for the soul.

173
00:19:40,164 --> 00:19:42,577
And the Afternoon Prayer is another meal.

174
00:19:42,577 --> 00:19:47,050
And the Sunset Prayer is an meal, nutrition
for the real person.

175
00:19:47,050 --> 00:19:53,027
And the Night Contact Prayer is the dinner
for the soul.

176
00:19:53,027 --> 00:20:00,000
So, nourishing, developing and growing the
soul is the reason for observing the Contact

177
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:04,816
Prayers, and we are the ones who need it. God
does not need it.

178
00:20:19,330 --> 00:20:26,876
All practices of worship in Islam, without
exception, are designed to cause the soul,

179
00:20:26,876 --> 00:20:30,650
the real person, the real you, to grow and
develop.

180
00:20:30,650 --> 00:20:35,302
They're all designed to make you the boss
over your body.

181
00:20:35,302 --> 00:20:40,451
A lot of people, in fact the majority
of people, are enslaved to their body,

182
00:20:40,451 --> 00:20:44,820
their outer garment, that is temporary.

183
00:20:44,820 --> 00:20:52,260
Some day this garment is going to vanish
and you, the real person, will remain forever, for eternity.

184
00:20:52,260 --> 00:20:58,260
So, most people, unfortunately, are unaware
of nourishing and strengthening and developing

185
00:20:58,260 --> 00:21:00,389
their soul, the real person.

186
00:21:00,389 --> 00:21:08,200
But all practices of worship in Islam are
designed to cause the soul to grow and develop,

187
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,820
nourish the soul.

188
00:21:09,820 --> 00:21:13,920
For example, the Morning Prayer, let’s take
the Morning Contact Prayer.

189
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:19,030
Before sunrise, what does the body... what
does your body want?

190
00:21:19,030 --> 00:21:22,110
Your body wants to sleep, right?

191
00:21:22,110 --> 00:21:30,000
But your soul, you, the real you, the real
person, needs to get up, do the ablution,

192
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:37,820
and observe the Contact Prayer, make contact, the first contact of the day with your creator.

193
00:21:37,820 --> 00:21:43,960
So, immediately you can see that there is a fight.
The body wants to sleep, and the soul needs

194
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:49,112
to get up and nourish itself and have breakfast.

195
00:21:49,112 --> 00:21:56,790
Now, who's going to win? If your body wins, you continue to sleep.

196
00:21:56,790 --> 00:22:04,346
And the body is the temporary garment. It
is not very smart to let the body win, right?

197
00:22:04,346 --> 00:22:12,460
If you win, you, the real person, win, your
body will obey and will say “yes, sir”

198
00:22:12,460 --> 00:22:19,409
will listen to you, obey you, get up out of
bed, do the ablution, and observe the Contact Prayer.

199
00:22:19,409 --> 00:22:27,680
So, you can see that the first Contact Prayer
is a struggle between you and your body.

200
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:33,450
By the way, this struggle becomes less and
less, as your body becomes more and more obedient

201
00:22:33,450 --> 00:22:40,750
to you, as you become the boss. As you develop
and become stronger, your body becomes more and more

202
00:22:40,750 --> 00:22:46,929
obedient, and with time, your body, when
you say “my body get up and do the Morning

203
00:22:46,929 --> 00:22:49,536
Prayer”, your body will say “yes, sir”
obediently.

204
00:22:49,536 --> 00:22:57,962
As a matter of fact, eventually, you will actually
enjoy getting up in the morning and doing the Contact Prayer.

205
00:22:57,962 --> 00:23:04,500
And this is because the soul has grown and
developed, and became the boss, and enjoys

206
00:23:04,500 --> 00:23:07,814
observing the contact with our creator.

207
00:23:07,814 --> 00:23:13,520
You look at the fasting, for example. One of
the important practices in Islam is fasting

208
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:16,901
the month of Ramadan, during the month of
Ramadan.

209
00:23:16,901 --> 00:23:27,302
And, in Ramadan, your body, of course, wants to eat and drink, but you tell your body when you fast,

210
00:23:27,302 --> 00:23:30,290
“you're not gonna eat or drink until sunset.”

211
00:23:30,290 --> 00:23:37,060
So, you can see that you are practicing, exercising
your soul, and this causes your soul to grow

