message, the Quran, every day, the whole Quran,

410
00:43:02,430 --> 00:43:04,439
not just the short Suras.

411
00:43:04,439 --> 00:43:09,789
But in the Contact Prayers, please, you only
need recite Al-Fãtehah.

412
00:43:09,789 --> 00:43:14,640
And this is a unifying force of all the Muslims
in the world.

413
00:43:14,640 --> 00:43:20,720
I was praying in Mecca one time and the Imam
read Al-Fãtehah and then he read the whole

414
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:24,979
Sura number 32, Sura Al-Sajdah
after Al-Fãtehah.

415
00:43:24,979 --> 00:43:30,632
And I was thinking, you know, there are a few
thousands of people in there around the Ka‘bah

416
00:43:30,632 --> 00:43:35,279
praying behind this Imam, and the vast majority
of them didn’t know any Arabic.

417
00:43:35,279 --> 00:43:43,660
What is their point? They just stand through all
this recitation in Arabic that they do not understand.

418
00:43:43,660 --> 00:43:46,294
What is required is only recite Al-Fãtehah.

419
00:43:46,294 --> 00:43:51,160
And this will unify all the Muslims of the
world. They will do the same thing in all

420
00:43:51,160 --> 00:43:56,077
the prayer. In Japan, they know Al-Fãtehah.
They read it in the Contact Prayer. In Sweden,

421
00:43:56,077 --> 00:44:02,240
in America, in Canada, in Australia, in Mecca,
in Pakistan, all the Muslims of the world

422
00:44:02,240 --> 00:44:04,080
will do the same thing.

423
00:44:04,080 --> 00:44:10,670
But this business of reciting long portions
of the Quran is wrong. It actually ruins the

424
00:44:10,670 --> 00:44:16,980
Contact Prayer. God wants things to be easy
for us, but Satan wants to make things difficult

425
00:44:16,980 --> 00:44:23,371
for us. So, he adds all things. Besides,
when you recite the Quran, you mention Moses and

426
00:44:23,371 --> 00:44:27,606
Jesus and Muhammad and Pharaoh and the
devil and all these things.

427
00:44:27,606 --> 00:44:33,390
You'll mention other names besides the name of
God in the prayer, and this is forbidden by

428
00:44:33,390 --> 00:44:34,739
commandment from God.

429
00:44:34,739 --> 00:44:36,980
We are not to mention any name.

430
00:44:36,980 --> 00:44:42,420
When you recite the Quran in the mosque and
you mention other names, it's because God says

431
00:44:42,420 --> 00:44:48,045
so in the Quran. It says
(19:16) وَٱذْكُرْ فِى ٱلْكِتَـٰبِ مَرْيَمَ
for example. This is God’s commandment.

432
00:44:48,045 --> 00:44:55,000
You can mention the name of Mary in the Quran
in order to learn from the lessons of previous

433
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:57,700
prophets, messengers, and so on.

434
00:44:57,700 --> 00:45:03,020
And it is a commandment from God to mention. So, when we read the Quran, we mention these

435
00:45:03,030 --> 00:45:06,360
names only because God commanded us to do
so.

436
00:45:06,360 --> 00:45:12,780
But in the Contact Prayers, in the Salat,
we are commanded never to mention any other

437
00:45:12,780 --> 00:45:16,255
name but the name of Allah, the name of God.

438
00:45:38,050 --> 00:45:44,730
After you have done the Wuḍū and you are
ready for the prayer, you go to a nice clean

439
00:45:44,730 --> 00:45:50,350
place. You don’t necessarily need the
prayer rug. This is one of those innovations.

440
00:45:50,350 --> 00:45:57,789
You can pray in any clean place, even bare
ground as long as it is dry and clean.

441
00:45:57,789 --> 00:46:04,390
So, you go to a nice clean place and you find
the direction of Mecca, the direction of the

442
00:46:04,390 --> 00:46:09,560
Sacred Mosque, because this is
a commandment in Quran that you must face.

443
00:46:09,560 --> 00:46:15,960
This is an organizational point. There
is no other significance to it, except organizational.

444
00:46:15,960 --> 00:46:22,060
You can imagine people going in a mosque and
facing in different directions, it'll be a mess.

445
00:46:22,060 --> 00:46:28,660
So, this organizational point dictates on
us that we must face the direction of Mecca,

446
00:46:28,670 --> 00:46:30,300
wherever you might be.

447
00:46:30,300 --> 00:46:39,890
So, in the United States, the direction generally
is slightly south of east, slightly south

448
00:46:39,890 --> 00:46:42,440
of east, southeast.

449
00:46:42,440 --> 00:46:48,040
So, find the direction of Mecca. You face that
direction and then you make your intention.

450
00:46:48,040 --> 00:46:50,070
This is the first step.

451
00:46:50,070 --> 00:46:55,189
You must say “I intend to do the Morning Prayer”
in any language you like.

452
00:46:55,189 --> 00:47:01,210
If you want it in Arabic, you can say “Nawaytu
Salat Al-Sobh.” This will be the NIYYA or

453
00:47:01,210 --> 00:47:03,937
the intention for the Morning Prayer.

454
00:47:03,937 --> 00:47:11,690
Or if it is for the Noon Prayer, you say, in
your heart or in an audible voice “I intend

455
00:47:11,690 --> 00:47:16,750
to do the Noon Prayer”, “Nawaytu Salat
Al-Zuhr” in Arabic.

456
00:47:16,750 --> 00:47:22,520
If it is the Afternoon Prayer, it is “Nawaytu
Salat Al-Asr.”

457
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:29,600
And for the Sunset Prayer, the NIYYA or intention
is “Nawaytu Salat Al-Maghrib.”

458
00:47:29,600 --> 00:47:36,980
For the Night Prayer, the intention or the NIYYA
is “Nawaytu Salat Al-'Eshaa.”

459
00:47:36,980 --> 00:47:41,409
So, but you can do it in any language you
wish, secretly or loudly.

460
00:47:41,409 --> 00:47:46,450
Now after you do the NIYYA, now you're facing the direction of Mecca, you make your intention

461
00:47:46,450 --> 00:47:52,420
or NIYYA, then you open the Salat by raising
your hands to the sides of your face and saying

462
00:47:52,420 --> 00:47:57,500
“Allahu akbar” like this “Allahu akbar."

463
00:47:57,500 --> 00:48:00,435
There is your opening of the Salat.

464
00:48:00,435 --> 00:48:11,054
Once you say “Allahu Akbar” in this manner, you have started your contact or Salat, your contact with your creator.

465
00:48:11,054 --> 00:48:18,916
Now after you make the opening TAKBIR, Allahu akbar, you can either put your hands on the side

466
00:48:18,916 --> 00:48:22,369
or you can choose to hold them like
this, with your left hand

467
00:48:22,369 --> 00:48:27,450
on your stomach, and your right
hand on top of your left hand. It doesn’t

468
00:48:27,450 --> 00:48:32,080
make any difference. Some people make a big
deal out of it, but there is no difference.

469
00:48:32,080 --> 00:48:33,856
Either way is correct.

470
00:48:33,856 --> 00:48:37,920
So, this is the opening of the Salat,
the Contact Prayer.

471
00:48:37,920 --> 00:48:41,040
Allahu akbar.

472
00:48:41,040 --> 00:48:46,215
Now, you are ready to recite Al-Fãtehah, the
opening Sura of Quran.

473
00:48:48,131 --> 00:48:55,820
The easiest way for you is to have me write the words in English transliteration, English letters.

474
00:48:55,820 --> 00:49:02,570
So, before you do the Wuḍū, the ablution,
you can say your intention “I intend to

475
00:49:02,570 --> 00:49:06,790
make the ablution” or Wuḍū either in
English or in Arabic.

476
00:49:06,790 --> 00:49:12,130
So “I intend to do the ablution” in English,
the Arabic would be “Nawaytu Al-Wuḍū”.

477
00:49:12,130 --> 00:49:28,720
And you write it like this “Nawaytu.”
“Nawaytu” which means “I intend.”

478
00:49:28,720 --> 00:49:32,620
Nawaytu Al-Wuḍū.

479
00:49:32,620 --> 00:49:35,439
“Al” means “the.”

480
00:49:35,439 --> 00:49:45,380
Ablution “Wuḍū”, “Al-Wuḍū.”

481
00:49:45,380 --> 00:49:50,522
“Nawaytu Al-Wuḍū”

482
00:49:50,522 --> 00:49:58,460
Let me write the words of Azaan for you. “Allahu
Akbar, Allahu Akbar, Allahu Akbar Allahu Akbar,

483
00:49:58,460 --> 00:50:00,540
La Elaha Ella Allah.”

484
00:50:00,540 --> 00:50:04,960
So, in the Azaan, we say “Allahu Akbar” 4 times.

485
00:50:04,960 --> 00:50:17,280
“Allahu Akbar“ meaning “God is 
the greatest.” Allahu

486
00:50:17,280 --> 00:50:30,000
“Allahu”, “God” “Akbar” (greatest).

487
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:36,380
Allahu Akbar, 4 times.

488
00:50:36,380 --> 00:50:39,139
Then, “La Elaha Ella Allah.”

489
00:50:39,139 --> 00:50:41,960
“La” means no.

490
00:50:44,120 --> 00:50:45,340
La

491
00:50:45,340 --> 00:50:53,640
“Elaha” meaning god with a small g.

492
00:51:00,900 --> 00:51:04,940
“La” means no. "Elaha" is god.

493
00:51:04,940 --> 00:51:06,380
no

494
00:51:06,380 --> 00:51:09,280
"Elaha" is god with a small g.

495
00:51:12,140 --> 00:51:15,140
“Ella” means except.

496
00:51:19,180 --> 00:51:23,460
"Ella", except

497
00:51:28,700 --> 00:51:39,300
"Allah"
means God.

498
00:51:43,264 --> 00:51:45,974
“La Elaha Ella Allah“

499
00:51:45,974 --> 00:51:53,460
So, this is the complete Azaan, the original
Azaan without any innovations or additions

500
00:51:53,460 --> 00:51:56,000
or traditions.

501
00:51:56,000 --> 00:52:02,640
A lot of people think that Allah is the name
of God, but it is not. Allah simply means God.

502
00:52:02,640 --> 00:52:05,700
The English word for it is God.

503
00:52:05,710 --> 00:52:11,500
The non-Muslims in the Arabic world say “Allah”
because this is the Arabic word for God

504
00:52:11,500 --> 00:52:13,376
even though they are not Muslims.

505
00:52:13,376 --> 00:52:18,900
They will say “IN SHAA ALLAH.” They say “Allah” and because 
simply that is the language.

506
00:52:18,900 --> 00:52:25,780
It is not the name of God. This is why I use
the word, the English word, “God” for "Allah."

507
00:52:28,140 --> 00:52:34,334
Allahu Akbar
Allahu Akbar

508
00:52:37,480 --> 00:52:44,054
Allahu Akbar
Allahu Akbar

509
00:52:45,440 --> 00:52:50,860
La Elaha Ella Allah

510
00:52:52,820 --> 00:52:57,780
I'm going to write the NIYYA or intention
for every prayer for you, so you can see how

511
00:52:57,780 --> 00:52:59,880
it is spelled.

512
00:52:59,880 --> 00:53:04,300
Here's the NIYYA or intention for the Morning
Prayer.

513
00:53:04,300 --> 00:53:16,940
“Nawaytu” – “Nawaytu” which means
“I intend."

514
00:53:16,940 --> 00:53:41,340
“Salat” – “Salat Al-Subh” – “Al”
– “Subh” – “Al-Subh”

515
00:53:41,340 --> 00:53:47,246
“I intend to do the Morning Prayer” – “Nawaytu
Salat Al-Subh.”

516
00:53:47,246 --> 00:53:56,131
Now, to make it the Noon Prayer, you just... you say the same thing except you change

517
00:53:56,131 --> 00:54:02,880
“Al-Subh” to “Zuhr” which means “noon.”

518
00:54:02,880 --> 00:54:07,640
“Nawaytu” – “Nawaytu Salat Al-Zuhr.”

519
00:54:07,640 --> 00:54:16,800
This will make it the Noon Prayer, “Al-Zuhr.”

520
00:54:16,800 --> 00:54:20,640
For the Afternoon Prayer, you just make it
“Al-'Asr”

521
00:54:20,640 --> 00:54:38,265
“Salat Al-'Asr.” You write 'A like this "Al-'Asr." “Nawaytu Salat Al-'Asr.”

522
00:54:38,265 --> 00:54:45,440
The Sunset, you make it “Al-Maghrib.”

523
00:54:45,440 --> 00:55:03,980
“Nawaytu Salat Al-Maghrib”, it's written
like this “Al-Maghrib.”

524
00:55:03,980 --> 00:55:08,599
“Nawaytu Salat Al-Maghrib.” This is the
Sunset Prayer.

525
00:55:08,599 --> 00:55:13,330
And the Night Prayer is “Al-'Eshaa.”

526
00:55:13,330 --> 00:55:27,220
“Nawaytu Salat Al-'Eshaa” – “Al-'Eshaa.”

527
00:55:27,220 --> 00:55:34,240
“Nawaytu Salat Al-'Eshaa.”

528
00:55:34,240 --> 00:55:42,920
By now you know how Allahu akbar is written,
the opening of the Contact Prayer “Allahu akbar."

529
00:55:42,920 --> 00:55:45,880
This is followed by Sura Al-Fãtehah.

530
00:55:45,880 --> 00:56:02,860
And it is written like this:
The first verse is “Bism Allah.”

531
00:56:02,860 --> 00:56:13,120
“Arrahman.”

532
00:56:13,120 --> 00:56:29,980
“Arraheem.”

533
00:56:29,980 --> 00:56:34,820
“Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem.”

534
00:56:34,820 --> 00:56:46,260
“Al hamdu”

535
00:56:46,260 --> 00:56:54,320
“Lillahi”

536
00:56:54,320 --> 00:57:14,340
“Rabbil ‘Alameen”

537
00:57:14,340 --> 00:57:21,380
Okay, “Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem”
means “in the name of God, most Gracious,

538
00:57:21,380 --> 00:57:23,760
most Merciful.”

539
00:57:23,760 --> 00:57:28,760
“Al hamdu Lillahi” means “praise be
to God."

540
00:57:28,760 --> 00:57:34,740
“Rabbil ‘Alameen” means “Lord of
the universe.”

541
00:57:34,740 --> 00:57:41,380
“Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem. Al hamdu
Lillahi Rabbil ‘Alameen”, “in the name

542
00:57:41,380 --> 00:57:49,080
of God, most Gracious, most Merciful. Praise
be to God, Lord of the universe.”

543
00:57:49,080 --> 00:58:12,880
And the next statement is familiar to you:
“Arrahman Arraheem”, “Most Gracious

544
00:58:12,880 --> 00:58:19,690
Most Merciful.”

545
00:58:19,690 --> 00:58:33,560
And the next statement is: “Maliki” means
“Master” or “King.”

546
00:58:33,560 --> 00:58:51,240
“Yawm” means day. “Eddeen”; recompense.
"Yawm Eddeen" day of recompense.

547
00:58:51,240 --> 00:58:57,120
So “Arrahman Arraheem”, “Most Gracious,
Most Merciful”, “Maliki Yawm Eddeen”,

548
00:58:57,120 --> 00:59:00,680
“Master of 
the Day of Recompense.”

549
00:59:00,680 --> 00:59:30,820
“Eyyaka Na’abudu” means “only You
we worship.”

550
00:59:30,820 --> 00:59:33,890
“Wa Eyyaka” means “and only You”

551
00:59:33,890 --> 00:59:36,340
“Wa” means “and.”

552
00:59:36,340 --> 00:59:59,900
“Eyyaka Nasta’aeen” means “we ask
for help, only You we ask for help.”

553
00:59:59,900 --> 01:00:07,510
“Wa Eyyaka Nasta’aeen”, “and only
You we ask for help.”

554
01:00:07,510 --> 01:00:15,959
The next statement... now, of course, you can
always go back, reverse the tape and watch

555
01:00:15,959 --> 01:00:24,226
all these words until you know them very
well by heart.

556
01:00:24,226 --> 01:00:31,080
The next statement is “Ehdina Al-Serata
Al-Mustaqeem”, “guide us in the right path."

557
01:00:31,080 --> 01:00:40,200
“Ehdina” means “guide us.”

558
01:00:40,200 --> 01:00:51,900
“Al-Serata” means “the path”.

559
01:00:51,900 --> 01:01:05,060
“Al-Mustaqeem”, “the straight” or
the right path.

560
01:01:08,140 --> 01:01:14,980
“Ehdina Al-Serata Al-Mustaqeem”, “guide
us in the right path.”

561
01:01:14,980 --> 01:01:26,920
“Serata” means “the path of”

562
01:01:26,920 --> 01:01:36,780
“Al-Lazeena” means “the path
of those”

563
01:01:36,780 --> 01:01:44,340
“An’amta” means “those whom You blessed.”

564
01:01:44,340 --> 01:01:55,260
“An’amta ‘Alayhim”, “You showered
Your blessings on them.”

565
01:01:55,260 --> 01:02:00,640
“Ehdina Al-Serata Al-Mustaqeem”, “guide
us in the right path.”

566
01:02:00,640 --> 01:02:09,640
“Serata Al-Lazeena An’amta ‘Alayhim”, 
“the path of those whom you blessed.”

567
01:02:09,640 --> 01:02:22,020
And then we go to the last statement in 
the Al-Fãtehah, “Ghayri Al-Maghdoobi ‘Alayhim.”

568
01:02:22,020 --> 01:02:31,120
“Ghayri” means “other than, or not.”

569
01:02:31,120 --> 01:02:54,060
“Al-Maghdoobi ‘Alayhim” means “not
the path of those who incur wrath, or anger.”

570
01:02:54,060 --> 01:02:56,780
“Ghayri Al-Maghdoobi ‘Alayhim.”

571
01:02:56,780 --> 01:02:58,080
“Wa Laddaalleen” (not the strayers).

572
01:02:58,080 --> 01:03:00,480
“Wa” means “and.”

573
01:03:00,480 --> 01:03:03,820
“La” means “no”, “nor” “Wa La”

574
01:03:03,820 --> 01:03:13,880
“Wa Laddaalleen”, and this is the end of
it – “and not the strayers.”

575
01:03:13,880 --> 01:03:18,460
“Ghayri Al-Maghdoobi ‘Alayhim”, “not
the path of those who incur wrath, or anger”

576
01:03:18,460 --> 01:03:22,550
“Wa Laddaalleen”, “nor the strayers.”

577
01:03:42,960 --> 01:03:48,474
After you recite Al-Fãtehah, then you make Ruku, bowing.

578
01:03:48,474 --> 01:03:54,554
And as you bow you say “Allahu Akbar”
and you know what that looks like. I wrote it for you.

579
01:03:54,554 --> 01:04:00,240
Then during the Ruku you say “Subhaana Rabbiya
Al-‘Azeem” about three times. It doesn’t

580
01:04:00,240 --> 01:04:02,500
matter, two or three or four times.

581
01:04:02,500 --> 01:04:12,300
“Subhaana” means “glory be to.”

582
01:04:12,300 --> 01:04:22,500
“Subhaana Rabbiya” means “Glory be
to my Lord.”

583
01:04:22,500 --> 01:04:31,560
“Al-‘Azeem” means “the Great.”

584
01:04:31,560 --> 01:04:38,700
“Subhaana Rabbiya Al-‘Azeem”, “Glory
be to my Lord, the Great.”

585
01:04:38,700 --> 01:04:47,100
Then, you stand up and in this position only
you say “Sami’a Allahu Leman Hamidah”

586
01:04:47,100 --> 01:04:50,980
means “God hears anyone who praises Him.”

587
01:04:50,980 --> 01:05:09,820
And it is written like this
“Sami’a Allahu”

588
01:05:09,820 --> 01:05:17,220
“Leman”, “anyone.”

589
01:05:17,220 --> 01:05:25,480
“Hamidah”, “who praises him.”

590
01:05:25,480 --> 01:05:31,140
“Sami’a Allahu Leman Hamidah” as you
stand up.

591
01:05:31,140 --> 01:05:39,400
Then, you make the first prostration, Sujud.

592
01:05:39,400 --> 01:05:44,160
And when you do that, you say “Allahu Akbar”
as you go down in prostration.

593
01:05:44,160 --> 01:05:58,640
And during prostration, you say
“Subhaana Rabbiya Al-A‘alaa”

594
01:05:58,640 --> 01:06:05,920
about three or four times, means “Glory be to my lord,
the Most High.”

595
01:06:05,930 --> 01:06:09,002
“Al-A‘alaa”, “the Most High.”

596
01:06:09,002 --> 01:06:13,900
And this takes care of all the words of the
Contact Prayers.

597
01:06:13,900 --> 01:06:19,420
Now, you know how to say all the words and
if you play the tape over and over, you can

598
01:06:19,420 --> 01:06:23,653
see how exactly they are written down and
how they are pronounced.

599
01:07:17,440 --> 01:07:24,840
In the sitting position, you say “Ash-hadu
Alla Elaha Ella Allah, Wahdahu La Shareeka Lah"

600
01:07:24,840 --> 01:07:30,000
which means “I bear witness that
there is no god except Allah, the one God,

601
01:07:30,000 --> 01:07:30,940
He is one.

602
01:07:30,940 --> 01:07:33,050
“La Shareeka Lah”, “He has no partners.” 

603
01:07:33,050 --> 01:07:43,620
And this is how I write it
“Ash-hadu” means “I bear witness.”

604
01:07:43,620 --> 01:07:49,066
“Ash-hadu Alla”,

605
01:07:49,066 --> 01:07:53,860
“Elaha” means “god with a small g.”

606
01:07:53,860 --> 01:07:56,660
“I bear witness that there is no god”

607
01:07:56,660 --> 01:08:01,880
“Ella”, “except”

608
01:08:01,880 --> 01:08:08,160
“Ella Allah”, “the one God”

609
01:08:08,160 --> 01:08:18,859
“Wahdahu”, “He is one”

610
01:08:18,860 --> 01:08:22,900
“Wahdahu La Shareeka Lah”, “He has
no partner.”

611
01:08:22,900 --> 01:08:25,280
“La” means “no.”

612
01:08:25,280 --> 01:08:28,260
“Shareek” means “partner.”

613
01:08:28,260 --> 01:08:38,860
“La Shareeka Lah”, (He has no partner).

614
01:08:38,860 --> 01:08:44,440
And this takes care of the Ta-shahud in the
sitting position,

615
